<title>USA: IVAX's generic captopril cleared by FDA.</title>
<headline>IVAX's generic captopril cleared by FDA.</headline>
<dateline>MIAMI 1996-09-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>IVAX Corp said Thursday the U.S. Food and Drug Administration approved an abbreviated new drug application for the generic pharmaceutical product captopril in 12.5, 25, 50 and 100 mg tablets.</p>
<p>Captopril is indicated for the treatment of hypertension, and is the generic equivalent of Bristol-Myers Squibb Co's Capoten.</p>
<p>The product is expected to be marketed by IVAX's Zenith Goldline Pharmaceuticals Inc subsidiary, the company said.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610.</p>
